WI-3: Identify the 20 newly-running tests by name. From WI-2's
output, produce a per-test enumeration:

For each newly-running test (the test was skipped at
 and passes at ), record:
  a) fully-qualified test path
     (path/to/test_file.py::TestClass::test_method);
  b) the marker / skip-condition at 
     (verbatim @pytest.mark expression);
  c) the marker / skip-condition at 
     (verbatim @pytest.mark expression);
  d) the commit (or commit set) responsible for the change
     (commit hash + one-line message);
  e) classification:
     - skip-condition-relaxed (the skipif predicate now
       evaluates False where it was True before);
     - marker-renamed (the marker name changed and is now
       collected where it was filtered before);
     - fixture-newly-available (a fixture the skip depended on
       is now provided);
     - environment-resolved (an env var or installed package the
       skip depended on is now present in the test environment);
     - dependency-resolved (an optional dependency is now
       installed);
     - other (specify in prose).

Render as a Markdown table in SS3 of the report; >= 20 rows (or
the actual count if not exactly 20; document the asymmetry).

Read-only inspection of test source. NO test file is edited.
